spaCy is an open-source software library for advanced Natural Language Processing (NLP) in Python. 
It's designed to be fast, efficient, and highly accessible, making it a popular choice for building NLP applications.
spaCy excels in tasks like part-of-speech tagging, named entity recognition, dependency parsing, and more. 
It supports multiple languages and offers pre-trained models for various NLP tasks, optimized for both performance and accuracy. 
Its design is geared towards practical, real-world applications and it's widely used in industry
and academia for building NLP pipelines and applications. It’s becoming increasingly popular for processing 
and analyzing data in the field of NLP.
Unstructured text is produced by companies, governments, and the general population at an incredible scale. It’s often important to automate the processing and analysis of text that would be impossible for humans to process. To automate the processing and analysis of text, you need to represent the text in a format that can be understood by computers. spaCy can help you do that.
